  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle then pat the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> dry with kitchen roll and season the skin generously with <strong>salt</strong></p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken thighs</strong>, skin-side down, and cook for 10 min or until the skin is golden and crispy (you'll finish cooking them later!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2078.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2078.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2078.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2078.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2078.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Top, tail and finely dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (skins on)</p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> roughly</p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2078.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2078.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2078.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2078.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2078.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken skin is crispy, transfer the chicken to a plate, set aside for later and return the <span class=\"text-highlight\">pan and oil to a m</span>edium heat</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>carrot</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>mushrooms, rosemary &amp; thyme sprigs</strong> and <strong>bay leaves </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until softened</p>\n<p>Tip: Add a drizzle of olive oil if it's looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2078.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
